  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do people like watching on YouTube?",
  "response": "People enjoy a wide variety of content on YouTube, catering to diverse interests and preferences. Here are some of the most popular types of content that people like watching:\n\n### 1. **Entertainment**\n   - **Comedy Skits & Vlogs**: Funny, relatable, and lighthearted content.\n   - **Reaction Videos**: People reacting to movies, music, or viral trends.\n   - **Pranks & Challenges**: Social experiments, pranks, or extreme challenges.\n   - **Celebrity Content**: Interviews, behind-the-scenes, or personal vlogs.\n\n### 2. **Music & Dance**\n   - **Music Videos**: Official music videos, lyric videos, or covers.\n   - **Dance Tutorials & Performances**: Choreography, dance challenges, or freestyle performances.\n\n### 3. **Gaming**\n   - **Gameplay Walkthroughs**: Tutorials, tips, or full gameplays.\n   - **Live Streams**: Real-time gaming sessions with live commentary.\n   - **Esports**: Competitive gaming tournaments and highlights.\n\n### 4. **Educational Content**\n   - **Tutorials**: DIY, tech, software, or skill-based tutorials.\n   - **Documentaries**: Informative and in-depth explorations of various topics.\n   - **Explainer Videos**: Science, history, or how-it-works content.\n\n### 5. **Lifestyle & Beauty**\n   - **Makeup Tutorials**: Beauty tips, product reviews, or transformations.\n   - **Fitness & Health**: Workout routines, diet plans, or wellness advice.\n   - **Travel Vlogs**: Exploring new places and sharing experiences.\n\n### 6. **Tech & Gadgets**\n   - **Unboxings & Reviews**: First impressions and detailed reviews of products.\n   - **Tech News**: Updates on the latest technology and innovations.\n   - **How-To Guides**: Fixing, upgrading, or using tech gadgets.\n\n### 7. **Food & Cooking**\n   - **Recipe Tutorials**: Step-by-step cooking or baking guides.\n   - **Food Challenges**: Eating large quantities or unusual foods.\n   - **Restaurant Reviews**: Exploring and reviewing eateries.\n\n### 8. **ASMR & Relaxation**\n   - **ASMR Videos**: Whispering, tapping, or soothing sounds for relaxation.\n   - **Meditation & Mindfulness**: Guided sessions for stress relief.\n\n### 9. **News & Commentary**\n   - **Current Events**: Discussions on politics, society, or global issues.\n   - **Opinion & Analysis**: Personal takes on trending topics.\n\n### 10. **Kids Content**\n   - **Cartoons & Animations**: Fun and educational videos for children.\n   - **Toy Unboxings**: Reviews and playtime with toys.\n\n### 11. **Art & Creativity**\n   - **Speed Drawing/Painting**: Artists showcasing their creative process.\n   - **Crafting Tutorials**: DIY projects and creative ideas.\n\n### 12. **Sports**\n   - **Highlights & Recaps**: Best moments from sports events.\n   - **Training & Tips**: Advice for improving athletic skills.\n\n### 13. **Viral & Trending Content**\n   - **Memes & Shorts**: Funny, bite-sized videos.\n   - **TikTok Compilations**: Popular clips from other platforms.\n\n### 14. **Personal Development**\n   - **Motivational Speeches**: Inspirational content to boost confidence.\n   - **Productivity Tips**: Strategies for time management and efficiency.\n\n### 15. **Shorts & Micro-Content**\n   - **Quick, Engaging Videos**: Short, snappy clips that grab attention.\n\nYouTube\u2019s algorithm also plays a role in suggesting content based on individual viewing habits, so trends can vary widely depending on the audience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
